## The Main Theories

### The "Skin of the God" theory

According to this hypothesis, the Dwemer were indeed transformed — not into gods, but into the very substance of the Numidium. Their collective being became the "divine metal" of which the golem is composed. They would still exist, in some fashion, but in a form so radically different that they are no longer recognizable as living beings.

### The "Absolute Zero" theory

Other scholars suggest that Kagrenac attempted to reach what metaphysicists call the "Zero" — the point of non-existence that precedes and underlies all reality. The Dwemer would have reached a state of existence-nonexistence that escapes all mortal comprehension.

### The lesson of the Dwemer

Whatever the truth, the disappearance of the Dwemer carries a warning that Tamriel has never forgotten: there are forces in this world that no intelligence, however brilliant, can safely control. The Dwemer were the greatest minds Tamriel ever produced — and their very genius caused their undoing.
